Just to be explicit, for not-so-techies like me, the WordPress theme is not implementing 'page.php' (Just as Christian Wach has explained). Our theme uses 'templates/front-page.php' So we simply need to add the code snippet above to the bottom of your theme's "functions.php" file. The "_some condition is met_" can be as follows: `add_filter( 'civicrm_basepage_template', 'use_my_own_template_for_civi' );
function use_my_own_template_for_civi( $template ) {
    if ( $template=='page.php' ) {
        return 'templates/front-page.php';
    }
    return $template;
}`

